&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;mfib&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; is still $O(2^n)$! If a function has already been fixed as a fix point, we cannot change its complexity!
Therefore there&#x27;s no way we can reuse &lt;code&gt;fib&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applying the fix point combinator, we can abstract the function itself:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
