&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Golang has no sum type!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People like to say that golang lacks &lt;em&gt;sum types&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;.
For example, in Rust we can write a simple &lt;code&gt;Result&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; type:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#212733;color:#ccc9c2;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#ffa759;&quot;&gt;enum &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#73d0ff;&quot;&gt;Result&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lt;T, E&amp;gt; {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:italic;color:#5ccfe6;&quot;&gt;Ok&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(T)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#ccc9c2cc;&quot;&gt;,
